President Cyril Ramaphosa will host Nigerian President Muhammadu Buhari on a state visit starting October 3 that will focus on trade and investment between Africa’s two biggest economies. Read: Hundreds of Nigerians to take free evacuation from SA The talks between the presidents also come just weeks after a spate of xenophobic violence flared up in South Africa and caused Nigeria to repatriate some of its citizens. © 2019 Bloomberg L.P.